# Data-Layer Enums

Enums follow one pattern end to end (exemplar: `allProjectStatuses` in `src/Data/Project/Project.ts`):

- Declare an `as const` array named `all<Xyz>s` and derive the union type from it:

```ts
export const allProjectStatuses = ["ACTIVE", "ARCHIVED"] as const
export type ProjectStatus = (typeof allProjectStatuses)[number]
```

- The column uses `text("status", { enum: allProjectStatuses })` — never a Postgres `ENUM` type.
- The SQL migration mirrors the values with a `CHECK (status IN (...))` constraint, and the Drizzle table declares the same `check(...)` so drift-check stays green.
- The matching GraphQL `enum` in `Graphql/` lists the same values; keep them in sync manually (drift shows up as codegen type errors).

# Avoid Redundant Zod Enum Validation

- When using `createInsertSchema`/`createUpdateSchema`, do not add explicit `z.enum(...)` overrides for columns that already declare `text("...", { enum: values })` — drizzle-zod infers them.
- Keep overrides focused on fields that genuinely need custom validation.
